-- STATS ChipPAC says Chinese bidders have approached it for acquisition
-- By Saeed Azhar
-- Wed Aug 27, 2014 07:38PM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, Aug 28 (Reuters) - STATS ChipPAC Ltd <STTS.SI> said on Thursday China's Jiangsu Changjiang Electronics Technology Co <600584.SS> and  Tianshui Huatian Technology Co <002185.SZ> are among parties who have approached the company for a possible acquisition.

STATS ChipPAC, which is majority owned by state investor Temasek Holdings, reiterated its earlier statements in May and June that it had been contacted by certain parties for a possible acquisition. "The company wishes to confirm that these parties include JCET and Huatian. There is no assurance that any of these approaches will result in any definitive agreement or transaction," the company said in a statement.